no-empty-label.description:
Description

This error occurs when a label is used to mark a statement that is not an iteration or switch

Example ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-empty-label: "error"*/

labeled:
var x = 10;

Example ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-empty-label: "error"*/

labeled:
for (var i=10; i; i--) {
    // ...
}
